The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, Sept. 2: Bengal will get its first integrated textile park set up by the Eastern India Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Federation. The foundation stone of the Rs 400-crore park was laid by Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee and Union textile minister Shankar Singh Vaghela at Mahishbatan near Sector V in Salt Lake. The park will commence production within the next 18 months.                            
	 Talegaon, Sept. 2: General Motors (GM) will triple its production of cars in India with the inauguration of its second plant at Talegaon near Pune. The company plans to raise production in the country to 2,25,000 vehicles a year.                            
	 Bangalore, Sept. 2: Kingfisher Airlines will be raising $400 million as equity by March 31 next year. Whether this will be in the form of convertible or straight equity has to be decided, company chairman Vijay Mallya said.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 2: Bombay Dyeing is looking at earning a revenue of Rs 900-crore through the sale of 4,50,000-square-foot of commercial space.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: IOC plans to spend over Rs 12,000 crore in upgrading its refineries to be compliant with Euro-IV emission standards by April 2010. All our refineries are on schedule to meet the Euro-III and Euro-IV deadline, IOC director (refineries) B.N. Bankapur said.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 2: Bosch Ltds German parent will buy back shares at a price not exceeding Rs 4,500 apiece, the company said in a filing to the BSE. The proposed buyback will entail Robert Bosch to buy shares from the open market through the stock exchange.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: The Ashok Minda group has acquired German firm Schenk Plastic Solutions for an undisclosed amount. We have purchased 100 per cent equity capital of Schenk through an all cash transaction, group chairman Ashok Minda said.                                                                                                                         
